ptember 2009}}\n\n<!-- If you are going to list your college or university, please indicate the Catholic religious institute that manages it. -->\nThe following is a '''list of Roman Catholic schools, colleges and universities in the Philippines'''. The church has more than 160 colleges and universities. Most of the [[Roman Catholic]] [[religious institute (Catholic)|religious institute]]s have their own schools. These include:\n==[[Congregation of the Mission]] or (Vincentian)==\n*[[Adamson University]], Manila\n*[[Universidad de Santa Isabel]], Naga, Camarines Sur\n*[[Santa Isabel College Manila]]\n*[[Colegio de San Jose]], Iloilo City\n\n==Congregation of Missionaries, Sons of the Immaculate Heart of the Blessed Virgin Mary or [[Claretians]]==\n* Claret College of Isabela City \n* [[Claret School of Quezon City]]\n* Claret School of Zamboanga City\n* Claret School of Lamitan City\n* Claret School of Maluso\n* Claret School of Tumahubong\n\n==[[Congregatio Immaculati Cordis Mariae]] or (CICM)==\n*[[University of Saint Louis Tuguegarao]], Cagayan\n*[[Saint Louis University (Philippines)|Saint Louis University]], Baguio City\n*[[Saint Louis College La Union]], San Fernando\n*[[Saint Mary's University (Philippines)|Saint Mary's University]], Bayombong, Nueva Vizcaya\n*[[Maryhill School of Theology]], Quezon City\n\n==[[List of Catholic dioceses in the Philippines|Diocese]]==\n*[[University of the Assumption]], San Fernando Pampanga\n*[[Father Saturnino Urios University]], Butuan\n*[[Saint Ferdinand College]], Ilagan\n\n==Dominican Sisters of St. Catherine of Siena==\n*Siena College of Hermosa\n*[[Siena College of Quezon City]]\n*Siena College of San Jose\n*[[Siena College of Taytay]]\n*Siena College of Tigaon\n*[[Holy Trinity University]]\n*Holy Rosary School of Pardo\n*[[Santa Catalina College|Santa Catalina College Manila]]\n*Santa Catalina College Binan Laguna\n*Notre Dame-Siena College of General Santos City\n*Notre Dame-Siena College of Polomolok\n*Notre Dame-Siena College of Tacurong\n\n==Dominican Sisters of the Trinity==\n*[[San Pedro College]]\n*St. James Academy\n\n==Immaculati Cordis Mariae/Missionary Sisters of the Immaculate Heart of Mary (''Immaculati Cordis Mariae'' or ICM)==\n*[[Saint Theresa's College of Quezon City]]\n*[[Saint Theresa's College of Cebu]]\n*[[St. Augustine School]], Tagudin, Ilocos Sur\n*[[Christ the King College (La Union)|Christ the King College]], San Fernando, La Union\n\n==[[Independent school|Independent]]==\n*[[Angeles University Foundation]], Angeles\n*[[Holy Angel University]], Angeles\n*[[University of Saint Anthony]], Iriga\n\n==[[Institute of the Brothers of the Christian Schools]] (''Fratres Scholarum Christianarum'' or FSC; LaSallian)==\n{{Main article|De La Salle Philippines}}\nAlso see<ref>http://delasalle.ph/schools/dls-csb</ref>\n*[[De La Salle University]], Manila\n*[[De La Salle University \u2013 Dasmari\u00f1as]]\n*[[De La Salle Araneta University]], Malabon City\n*[[De La Salle Andres Soriano Memorial College]] (DLSASMC), Lutopan, Toledo City, Cebu\n*[[De La Salle Santiago Zobel School|De La Salle Santiago Zobel]], Ayala Alabang, Muntinlupa\n*[[De La Salle Lipa]]\n*[[De La Salle\u2013College of Saint Benilde]] - [[Taft Avenue|Taft]] & [[Antipolo City|Antipolo]]\n*[[De La Salle John Bosco College]]\n*[[De La Salle Canlubang]]\n*[[De La Salle Medical and Health Sciences Institute]]\n*[[Jaime Hilario Integrated School \u2013 La Salle]]\n*[[La Salle University (Ozamiz, Philippines)|La Salle University]], Ozamiz\n*[[La Salle Green Hills]]\n*[[La Salle Academy (Philippines)|La Salle Academy]]\n*[[La Salle College Antipolo]]\n*[[University of St. La Salle]], Bacolod\n\n==[[Marist Brothers|Little Brothers of Mary]] (''Fratres Maristae a Scolis'' or FMS; Marist)==\n*[[Marist School (Marikina)|Marist School]]\n*[[Notre Dame of Dadiangas University]], General Santos\n*[[Notre Dame of Marbel University]], Koronadal\n\n==[[Missionaries of La Salette]]==\n*[[University of La Salette]], 